Title: New option for ignoring TCP RST packets as "host up" indication
Level: 1
Edition: cee
Component: cmc
Class: feature
Compatible: compat
State: unknown
Version: 1.4.0i1
Date: 1455627408

Some routers/firewalls send a TCP RST for a host which is known to be down,
using the source IP of the host in question.  Enabling the new "Ignore TCP
Reset Packets" flag under "Global Settings/Monitoring Core/Tuning of Smart
PING" prevents Smart PING from considering such a host as being up.
